               <div>
                  <h3 class="content-text">Image Processing</h3>
                  <ul style="list-style: none;">
                     <li>
                        Image Segmentation for foreground(Region of Interest) separation from background in digital images. Implemented non interactive segmentation using:
                        <ol>
                           <li> <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GrabCut">Grab Cut.</a>
                           </li>
                           <li>Edge Detection and approximating contour of RoI (foreground) for segmentation.</li>
                           <li>Binary Thresholding of digital images for quick mask based segmentation.</li>
                        </ol>
                     </li>
                     <br>
                     <li>
                        Dominant Colour detection in digital images. Implemented techniques:
                        <ol>
                           <li> Histogram based colour frequency calculation by converting image in human compatible HSV colour space. Filtering out colours with high frequency of occurrence as dominant colours.</li>
                           <li>
                              Colour data clustering using
                              <bold> K Means</bold>
                              . Segmented cluster centroids were used to approximate RGB values and classified as dominant colours.
                           </li>
                        </ol>
                     </li>
                     <br>
                     <li>
                        Out of focus Detection in digital images:
                        <ol>
                           <li>Calculated various figure of merits classified as local (pertaining to individual block in image) as well as Global (calculated using local figure of merits) and worked on implementation of feedback based tunable decision tree to detect if image is in focus or not.</li>
                           <li> Most work in this regard was based on research paper published by <a href="http://hplabs.hp.com/techreports/2005/HPL-2005-14.pdf">Lim, Wu, Yen</a> from HP Image Labs.</li>
                        </ol>
                     </li>
                     <br>
                     <li>
                        Implemented image processing backend java application using play framework at Roposo:
                        <ol>
                           <li> Capable of handling upto 500,000 images per instance per day.</li>
                           <li> Capable of resizing, perform compression, transcoding (whenever transcoding provided better results than compression for e.g. <a href="https://developers.google.com/speed/webp/">Webp</a>).</li>
                           <li> Capable of transcoding user uploaded videos to formats providing more compression benefit. Used FFMPEG for transcoding to formats like <a href="https://www.webmproject.org/">Webm</a>, optimised MP4, etc.</li>
                           <li> Uses most popular Image Processing and Computer Vision libraries like, OpenCV, MetadataExtractor, Libjpeg 9-c, Libpng, libwebp, gifsicle, imagemagick, exiftool, etc. </li>
                        </ol>
                        <ol>This involved working with AWS services like S3, SQS, Elastic Transcoder, CloudFront. For backend database MongoDB was used. This project also involved development of various testing modules using nodejs and bash for visual verification of experiments conducted. </ol>
                     </li>
                  </ul>
                  </p>
