               <div>
                  <h3 class="content-text">Electronic Support System For Speech Impairment (IEDC FUNDED) - NIT Hamirpur, H.P.</h3>
                  <ul style="list-style: none;">
                     <li>Worked on IEDC (Innovation and Enterprenurship Development Center) funded project aimed at developing electronic support system for speech impaired people.
                     </li>
                     <ol>
                        <li> This project involved working with sensor networks along with on board signal processing and microcontroller device.</li>
                        <li> Programmed MSP-430 for digitising sensor signals, filtering them and finally look up for gestures signatures in a look up table.
                        </li>
                        <li> With this project we were able to identify gestures in seven different orientations which could be tuned to be used with different sign languages.
                        </li>
                        <li> The final version of the product could decypher around 50 signs of most importance in Indian Sign Language.</li>
                     </ol>
                  </ul>
